nl_problem:
# Task: permutations_with_duplicates
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: permuteUnique(self, arg1)

Given a collection of numbers, nums, that might contain duplicates, return all possible unique permutations in any order.

Constraints:
- 1 <= nums.length <= 8
- -10 <= nums[i] <= 10
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "permuteUnique")
  (signature ( (nums list) ) list)
  (constraints
    (constraint "1 <= length(nums) <= 8")
    (constraint "-10 <= nums[i] <= 10")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Return all possible unique permutations of the given collection of numbers.")
    (rule "Ensure that duplicates are not included in the output.")
    (return "A list of lists, where each inner list represents a unique permutation of the input numbers.")
  )
)
